snippet.textDisplay: I am a fan from China. Kobe's spirit inspired me from my high school time until now when I graduated as a Master. He told me the definition of dedication, hard working and passion. He is absolutely a perfectionist and a man who cannot take the pain of loss in any kind of competition, so do I. I remember once he replied to one comment on money and passion that 'do what u love best, then money follows, that's a simple math question.' I felt kind of guilty after reviewing some videos on Kobe, because I nearly choose my career as what my parents suggested, not what I truly loved. After these videos, I think I know where actually to go, whatever how tough it is during the journey. Life is fucking short and thanks,Kobe. I appreciate you forever for your unbeatable heart. I will tell your story to my next generation.

snippet.textDisplay:
HOW KOBE IMPACTED ME!👇🏼

I grew up loving Kobe & hating on LeBron for no real reason. I fought almost every day for Kobe in school over debates of who is better between he & Bron to the point where people nicknamed me 'Kobe'. Most people didn’t know me if they didn’t play ball but they knew everyone called me Kobe so it got to a point where most people didn’t even know my real name.

Let me set the scene real quick. I’m in 7th grade & my parents couldn’t afford nice clothes for me let alone nice shoes. I used to hoop in some all grey with a red sole adidas generic shoe that costs probably less than 40 dollars. Everyone flamed me & jokingly made fun of me because all I focused on was basketball yet I never had a 'real' hooping shoe. My birthday is August 23rd just like Kobe. School always started around September 2nd so for my birthday I wanted to go in to the new school year with some fresh hooping sneaks & the 1 thing I asked for was Kobe’s. My mom actually got me the Kobe 7s System Supreme colorway & I made sure I didn’t touch them until the first day of school.

I remember walking into school for the first day kinda nervous of how people would react when they see me walk in with some nice sneaks. As I walk in the school the cafeteria is to my right & the gym is to my left. On some occasions my school security guard would let the hoopers sneak into the gym & ball until first period came which is about 30 mins to ball. When I walk into the gym I see all the friends I ball with. They all look at me, the balls stop bouncing & they all run towards me yelling & laughing in a fun manner because I finally got some ball sneaks. I remember that day like it was yesterday, it brung so much joy in my heart.

I finally graduate middle school everything is basically the same as far as how I feel about Kobe. As I go into high school NOBODY from my middle school elected to go to the same high school I went to. That means nobody knows me as Kobe anymore. Just a kid they’ve never seen before. Freshman year was cool I started forming my own opinions around what I like & who I follow. With that being said I never understood why I had so much hate towards LeBron. So I starting watching LeBron closely, probably even more than Kobe at the time & I started to appreciate him a lot more.

At this point the Lakers & Kobe played with the Dwight & Steve Nash squad that disappointed everyone due to injuries. Kobe injures his Achilles, Dwight moves on in free agency, Nash retires & the Lakers suck. At this point I was a big fan of Kyrie Irving & Kyrie was a mentee of Kobe so I decided, as Kobe goes out the door I’ll have my new fave player; Kyrie Irving. I eventually started claiming & watching all the cavs games. 2 years later LeBron comes home to Cleveland & my fandom for LeBron grew tremendously. As I was transitioning into high school, Kobe was transitioning into retirement.

As a Cleveland & Kyrie fan I had no choice but to watch LeBron closer than I ever have before. The flip switched, I now defended LeBron like I was defending Kobe in middle school.

It got so bad I started putting down Kobe’s greatness to justify how good I felt LeBron was. Especially after he won us a ring in 2016. I completely forgot about the man that made me love basketball. Just because I was too busy debating who was better between he & LeBron😔

Moral of my story is that “Comparison is the thief of joy”.... Both Kobe & LeBron brought me joy watching them play at both points of my young life but the day to day debates about who was better forced me to choose a side & I regret ever choosing one instead of fully appreciating both of them at the same time.

I Love You Kobe😥... I wouldn’t be able to write my life story without having the name Kobe Bryant written in it. Rest In Peace Icon😔🏀 #MambaMentality4Life
